]}, {\"sentence\": \"(IBJ photo/Mickey Shuey)  Shackell set a new personal best of 3:45.46, easily clearing the Olympic qualifying time.\", \"from\": 551, \"to\": 666, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 569, \"end\": 574, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Shuey\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shuey\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Shuey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Shuey\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Shackell trimmed 1.54-seconds off his previous best, set in 2023 at Summer Juniors.\", \"from\": 667, \"to\": 750, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Shackell is also competing in the 200 free, 200 fly, and 100 fly at the trials.\", \"from\": 752, \"to\": 831, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Luke Whitlock of Noblesville, who was the top qualifier in the men's 400-meter freestyle event during preliminary heats Saturday, finished fifth in the finals.\", \"from\": 833, \"to\": 992, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 833, \"end\": 837, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gospel_of_Luke\", \"score\": 0.9942936597926118, \"rank\": 0.0037067137511071044, \"text\": \"Luke\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gospel_of_Luke\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gospel_of_Luke\"}, {\"begin\": 838, \"end\": 846, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Whitlock\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.79946226230861e-15, \"text\": \"Whitlock\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Whitlock\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Max_Whitlock\"}, {\"begin\": 850, \"end\": 861, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noblesville_High_School\", \"score\": 0.999999983160251, \"rank\": 1.6331490545544533e-08, \"text\": \"Noblesville\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3914\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noblesville_High_School\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noblesville_High_School\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Also on Saturday, Katie Ledecky qualified for her fourth Olympics, cruising to victory in the 400-meter freestyle .\", \"from\": 994, \"to\": 1109, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1012, \"end\": 1025, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katie Ledecky\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Cheered on by a crowd of 20,689 at the home of the NFL's Indianapolis Colts, Ledecky touched the wall in 3 minutes, 58.35 seconds.\", \"from\": 1111, \"to\": 1241, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1162, \"end\": 1165, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Football_League\", \"score\": 0.951148635639326, \"rank\": 0.046871428927859025, \"text\": \"NFL\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Football_League\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Football_League\"}, {\"begin\": 1168, \"end\": 1186, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indianapolis_Colts\", \"score\": 0.9999984873886731, \"rank\": 1.2900046748438089e-06, \"text\": \"Indianapolis Colts\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indianapolis_Colts\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indianapolis_Colts\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She improved on her time of 3:59.99 in the morning preliminaries and set herself up to make a run at another gold against a loaded field at the Paris Games.\", \"from\": 1243, \"to\": 1399, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Australian \\\"Terminator,\\\" Ariarne Titmus, is the defending Olympic champion and world-record holder (3:55.38) in the 400 free.\", \"from\": 1401, \"to\": 1530, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1401, \"end\": 1415, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Australian\", \"score\": 0.9999999999972715, \"rank\": 2.7832770483777734e-12, \"text\": \"The Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Australian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Australian\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Canadian phenom Summer McIntosh is also expected to contend for the top spot on the podium.\", \"from\": 1531, \"to\": 1622, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1531, \"end\": 1539, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"score\": 0.9979823092265364, \"rank\": 0.0020209316978936336, \"text\": \"Canadian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\"}, {\"begin\": 1547, \"end\": 1562, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Summer_McIntosh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Summer McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Summer_McIntosh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Summer_McIntosh\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 27-year-old Ledecky is set to swim four events at her nation's trials, all of them freestyle events ranging from 200 to 1,500 meters.\", \"from\": 1624, \"to\": 1761, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She already has six individual gold medals-more than any female swimmer in Olympic history.\", \"from\": 1762, \"to\": 1853, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am pretty excited,\\\" Ledecky said after the victory ceremony.\", \"from\": 1855, \"to\": 1918, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I never imagined I would go to a fourth Olympic Games.\\\"\", \"from\": 1919, \"to\": 1975, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The expected second spot on the Olympic team will go to Paige Madden, the runner-up behind Ledecky at 4:02.08.\", \"from\": 1977, \"to\": 2087, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2033, \"end\": 2045, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paige_Madden\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paige Madden\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paige_Madden\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paige_Madden\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, Gretchen Walsh, a 21-year-old from the University of Virginia, set a world record in a semifinal heat of the 100-meter butterfly with a time of 55.18.\", \"from\": 2089, \"to\": 2250, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2100, \"end\": 2114, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gretchen_Walsh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gretchen Walsh\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gretchen_Walsh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gretchen_Walsh\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Swimmer Gretchen Walsh set a world record in the semifinal heat of the 100-meter butterfly with a time of 55.18 second.\", \"from\": 2252, \"to\": 2371, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2260, \"end\": 2274, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gretchen_Walsh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gretchen Walsh\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gretchen_Walsh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gretchen_Walsh\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(IBJ photo/Mickey Shuey)  Walsh was more than a half-second under world-record pace at the turn and finished strong to eclipse the mark of 55.48 set by Sweden's Sarah Sj\\u00f6str\\u00f6m at the 2016 Rio de Janeiro Olympics.\", \"from\": 2372, \"to\": 2584, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2390, \"end\": 2395, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Shuey\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shuey\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Shuey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Shuey\"}, {\"begin\": 2524, \"end\": 2530, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sweden_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"score\": 0.784387013876362, \"rank\": 0.198500501188331, \"text\": \"Sweden\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sweden_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sweden_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2533, \"end\": 2547, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Sj\\u00f6str\\u00f6m\", \"score\": 0.9999994657338511, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sarah Sj\\u00f6str\\u00f6m\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Sj\\u00f6str\\u00f6m\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Sj\\u00f6str\\u00f6m\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Walsh held her hand over her mouth as she looked at the scoreboard in disbelief, a \\\"WR\\\" beside her name.\", \"from\": 2586, \"to\": 2690, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But she's still got some work to do to make her first Olympic team.\", \"from\": 2691, \"to\": 2758, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 100 fly final Sunday night also includes Torri Huske, Regan Smith and Claire Curzan-all medalists at the Tokyo Games.\", \"from\": 2760, \"to\": 2881, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2805, \"end\": 2816, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Torri_Huske\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Torri Huske\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Torri_Huske\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Torri_Huske\"}, {\"begin\": 2818, \"end\": 2829, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Regan_Smith\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.54896432061418e-28, \"text\": \"Regan Smith\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Regan_Smith\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Regan_Smith\"}]}, {\"sentenc